## PB3.1: nested closure capture is rejected at the M20g layer.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 31 (PB3 post-impl review): a nested lambda
## that re-captures a name from the outer body's capture list
## (`fn |+sig| inner = fn |+sig| sig.get()`) is rejected in V1.
## The case is nontrivial — inner capture from `self.cap_<n>`,
## clone from capture field, inner env drop, possible nested
## retained closure — and Steve has deliberately deferred it
## until a real canary use case forces it.
##
## This example pins the rejection. If M20g's nested-capture
## rejection ever weakens, the PB3 audit's per-binding flag
## would still fire correctly for each layer of capture, BUT
## the emit machinery for capture-field plumbing through
## nested env structs isn't ready. Keep this test green to
## keep the V1 surface predictable.

sub main()
  sig: *Signal(Int) = *Signal(value: 0)
  outer = fn |+sig|
    inner = fn |+sig| sig.get()
    inner()
  outer()
